Definition :
  A class is a named group of properties and functions.
  Always starts with capital letter in java.
  A class is a logical construct.

pseudo :
  class Student{
    int rollno;
    String name;
    float marks;
  }

A class is a template of an object.
An object is a instance of class.

class - > logical construct
object - > physical reality

objects are stored in heap memory.
reference variables are stored in stack memory.

what is instance variables?
  Variables which are inside the object are known as instance varaibles.
